The paper deals with a communication system and proposes a new strategy for the downlink of communication systems. It involves splitting user messages and linearly precoding common and private streams at the transmitter, and opportunistically asking the relaying user to forward its decoded common message. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with resource allocation and optimization, which could also place it in the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. The paper also mentions compensating for performance degradation due to deep fading, which could place it in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The use of multiple antennas suggests that the paper could also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with cooperative strategies, which could place it in the Computer Communications (cs.COM) sub-category.
